## Partie 4 — Persistance des données MySQL

Un pod est éphémère : si MySQL redémarre sans volume, toutes les données sont perdues. Le **PersistentVolumeClaim** réserve du stockage durable.

Créez `mysql-pvc.yaml` :

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: mysql-pvc
  namespace: tp-app-mysql
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 1Gi
```

```bash
kubectl apply -f mysql-pvc.yaml
```

Vérifiez que le PVC est bien en statut `Bound` :

```bash
kubectl get pvc -n tp-app-mysql
```

---

## Partie 5 — Déploiement MySQL

Créez `mysql-deployment.yaml` :

```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: mysql
  namespace: tp-app-mysql
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: mysql
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: mysql
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: mysql
          image: mysql:8.0
          ports:
            - containerPort: 3306
          envFrom:
            - secretRef:
                name: mysql-secret
          volumeMounts:
            - name: mysql-storage
              mountPath: /var/lib/mysql
      volumes:
        - name: mysql-storage
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: mysql-pvc
```

```bash
kubectl apply -f mysql-deployment.yaml
```

Créez ensuite le Service interne `mysql-service.yaml` :

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: mysql
  namespace: tp-app-mysql
spec:
  selector:
    app: mysql
  ports:
    - port: 3306
      targetPort: 3306
  clusterIP: None
```

```bash
kubectl apply -f mysql-service.yaml
```

> 💡 `clusterIP: None` crée un **Service headless** : les autres pods pourront joindre MySQL simplement via le hostname `mysql`.
>

